article.headline: Wagner 72, Bryant 60
article.story: SMITHFIELD, R.I. -- Joey Mundweiler scored 20 points to pace Wagner in a 72-60 win over Bryant on Thursday night. The Seahawks (12-12,4-9 Northeast Conference) hit a season-best 12 3-point goals. Mundweiler hit 6 of 18 tries, and Chris Martin. who scored 18 points in 15 minutes of play, hit on 4 of 8. Bryant (7-18) got 19 points from Cecil Gresham and 17 from Adam Parzych. They led 33-31 at the half and by as many as seven points early in the second period before a 9-2 Wagner run to regain the lead. Chris Lambert's 3-point goal put Bryant up 54-52 with 9:33 left, but the Seahawks took the lead for good on Mundweiler's 3-pointer 33 seconds later. Bryant shot 10 of 27 from 3-point range. The loss snapped a three-game winning streak for the Bulldogs, in the first year of Division I play. They join the NEC in 2012.
